Name:           ghc-core
Version:        0.5.6
Release:        0
Summary:        Display GHC's core and assembly output in a pager
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  ghc-colorize-haskell-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-directory-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-filepath-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-pcre-light-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-process-devel

%description
A convenient command line wrapper for GHC that displays GHC's optimised core
and assembly output in a human readable, colourised manner, in a pager.
Unix systems only, currently.

Usage:

> ghc-core A.hs

> ghc-core -fvia-C -optc-O3 A.hs .


%prep
%setup -q

%build
%ghc_bin_build

%install
%ghc_bin_install

%files
%doc LICENSE
%doc README
%{_bindir}/%{name}

%changelog
